  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Meningitis is a rare complication following neurosurgical procedures and is associated with
      high morbidity and mortality. The aim of this study is to describe the clinical
      characteristics and microbiological characteristics in patients who develope meningitis
      following neurosurgical operations, and investigate the useful tips for the differential
      diagnosis of postneurosurgical meningitis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Besides description of characteristics of patients with postneurosurgical patients, we also
      will investigate the usefulness of prolonged cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) culture, and profiles
      of blood and CSF inflammatory markers for the differential diagnosis of meningitis. CSF
      culture will be extended upto 2 weeks. Serum procalcitonin and C-reactive protein, CSF
      adenosine deaminase levels will be monitored and analyzed for the differential diagnosis of
      meningitis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
